Package: vds
Version: @VERSION@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Jihong Min <hurryman2212@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: @INSTALLED_SIZE@
Depends: bluez, dkms, kmod, make, libc6, libbluetooth3, libdbus-1-3, libopus0, libstdc++6, libudev1
Recommends: logrotate
Suggests: linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-generic, clang, build-essential, pipewire, systemd, udev, wireplumber
Description: Virtual DualSense Bluetooth-to-USB bridge
 vDS exposes Bluetooth-connected DualSense-class controllers through a virtual
 USB controller so games and applications can use features normally available
 only over USB. The Debian package installs the userspace daemon, CLI, systemd
 unit, udev rule, and DKMS source for the Linux virtual USB HCD.
